body:
**Is this a BUG REPORT or FEATURE REQUEST?**: /kind bug **What happened**: I spun up a new K8s 1.9 on-prem cluster and added a mutating webhook: ```yaml apiVersion: admissionregistration.k8s.io/v1beta1 kind: MutatingWebhookConfiguration metadata: name: webhook-name webhooks: - name: webhook-name failurePolicy: Fail clientConfig: url: https://127.0.0.1:12345/auth/admit caBundle: ... rules: - operations: - "CREATE" - "UPDATE" apiGroups: - "*" apiVersions: - "*" resources: - "*" ``` I then tried to create a CRD: ``` apiVersion: apiextensions.k8s.io/v1beta1 kind: CustomResourceDefinition metadata: name: crontabs.stable.example.com spec: group: stable.example.com version: v1 scope: Namespaced names: plural: crontabs singular: crontab kind: CronTab shortNames: - ct ``` and got the error: ``` Error from server (InternalError): error when creating "crd.yml": Internal error occurred: no kind "CustomResourceDefinition" is registered for version "apiextensions.k8s.io/v1beta1" ``` If the CRD already exists, I get this error instead: ``` Error from server (InternalError): error when applying patch: {"metadata":{"annotations":{},"namespace":""},"spec":{"names":{}}} to: &{0xc420105080 0xc420178f50 crontabs.stable.example.com crd.yml 0xc4207597b8 628296 false} for: "crd.yml": Internal error occurred: no kind "CustomResourceDefinition" is registered for version "apiextensions.k8s.io/v1beta1" ``` **What you expected to happen**: ``` customresourcedefinition "crontabs.stable.example.com" created ``` or ``` customresourcedefinition "crontabs.stable.example.com" configured ``` **How to reproduce it (as minimally and precisely as possible)**: - Create a mutating webhook (like above. the endpoint doesn't need to exist as it is never hit). - Try to create a CRD (like above) - Failure **Anything else we need to know?**: Logs have this:
